Fig. 8F
); greatest height in front of the middle.

CpLl (
Fig. 8C
) slightly triangular due the presence of dorsal protuberance on RV; RV higher than LV; greatest height situated in the middle; anterior region broader than posterior; with pustules on anterior and posterior sides. CpRl (
Fig. 8D
